1
00:00:10,433 --> 00:00:11,600
<i> This is Six Feet Under Bar.</i>

2
00:00:11,733 --> 00:00:14,667
<i>This is also the known location
of the two female victims</i>

3
00:00:14,800 --> 00:00:15,767
<i> of human trafficking.</i>

4
00:00:15,900 --> 00:00:17,567
<i>Sir, we have an idea
for a sting operation.</i>

5
00:00:17,700 --> 00:00:19,400
<i>A potential victim will pose
as a target.</i>

6
00:00:19,533 --> 00:00:22,100
<i>The moment the criminals act,
we will arrest them on the spot.</i>

7
00:00:22,233 --> 00:00:22,900
<i> Lieutenant Conde.</i>

8
00:00:23,033 --> 00:00:24,500
<i> Bobby and I will go in.</i>

9
00:00:24,633 --> 00:00:26,833
<i>Wait for our call,
in case we need backup.</i>

10
00:00:26,967 --> 00:00:27,767
<i> It's noisy here.</i>

11
00:00:27,900 --> 00:00:28,733
<i> Do you want to go somewhere?</i>

12
00:00:28,867 --> 00:00:30,233
<i> Okay, okay, yeah.</i>

13
00:00:30,367 --> 00:00:31,233
<i> What's with you?</i>

14
00:00:31,367 --> 00:00:33,067
<i>- Ouch!
- Hey!</i>

15
00:00:33,200 --> 00:00:34,567
<i> Charlie, are you okay?</i>

16
00:00:34,733 --> 00:00:35,733
<i> What happened here?</i>

17
00:00:40,267 --> 00:00:41,500
<i>You thought I would do that,
didn't you?</i>

18
00:00:41,633 --> 00:00:42,733
<i> Charlie!</i>

19
00:00:42,867 --> 00:00:43,733
<i> Get down!</i>

20
00:00:44,800 --> 00:00:45,900
<i>Why did you throw away
my clutch bag?</i>

21
00:00:46,033 --> 00:00:46,833
<i> That's expensive!</i>

22
00:00:46,967 --> 00:00:48,333
<i> Perfect timing.</i>

23
00:00:48,467 --> 00:00:49,600
<i> Where are the suspects?</i>

24
00:00:49,733 --> 00:00:50,933
<i>It's done. The five suspects
are down.</i>

25
00:00:51,067 --> 00:00:52,033
<i> Sergeant Enriquez.</i>

26
00:00:52,167 --> 00:00:53,833
<i>I know you defended me earlier,</i>

27
00:00:53,967 --> 00:00:56,200
<i>but that doesn't mean
we're quits already.</i>

28
00:00:56,333 --> 00:00:57,033
<i> I know.</i>

29
00:00:57,167 --> 00:00:59,400
<i> Sir, the fingerprint analysis</i>

30
00:00:59,533 --> 00:01:02,233
<i>on the gun used to kill Vice
Mayor Del Mundo is ready.</i>

31
00:01:08,800 --> 00:01:12,000
Mar, Abdul, please give this
to grandmother.

32
00:01:12,133 --> 00:01:13,900
I need to go
to the police station.

33
00:01:14,033 --> 00:01:15,233
We'll take care of it, Bobby.

34
00:01:15,367 --> 00:01:16,300
Thank you.

35
00:01:16,433 --> 00:01:20,367
Hey, the turn of events
is terrible, Bobby.

36
00:01:20,500 --> 00:01:24,133
He's right and it seems like Amo
really does look guilty.

37
00:01:24,267 --> 00:01:28,067
We'll find out when the results
of the investigation come out.

38
00:01:28,200 --> 00:01:31,967
I feel the deaths
of Godmother Dina and Lara

39
00:01:32,100 --> 00:01:33,267
will soon be given justice.

40
00:01:33,400 --> 00:01:38,233
Well, Bobby, the question is,
what if Sir Tonyo finds out

41
00:01:38,367 --> 00:01:41,333
that Amo had something to do
with his girlfriend's death?

42
00:02:14,167 --> 00:02:18,333
So my suggestion is, next time,
can we do it at my place?

43
00:02:18,467 --> 00:02:22,533
I'll cook you anything,
even my mom's specialty.

44
00:02:22,667 --> 00:02:25,100
What's your mom's specialty?

45
00:02:25,233 --> 00:02:26,333
Me...

46
00:02:26,467 --> 00:02:29,667
Steamed, but I prefer it raw.

47
00:02:29,800 --> 00:02:33,667
Lieutenant Garcia, please,
let's focus on work for today.

48
00:02:37,467 --> 00:02:39,467
Matching residue
and a fingerprint

49
00:02:39,600 --> 00:02:41,300
were found on Victor's gun.

50
00:02:42,533 --> 00:02:43,867
Bok...

51
00:02:44,000 --> 00:02:45,133
that means he's the killer.

52
00:02:47,033 --> 00:02:48,567
Wait,

53
00:02:48,733 --> 00:02:52,333
they say the angle at which the
Vice Mayor was shot was low?

54
00:02:52,467 --> 00:02:53,200
Yes.

55
00:02:53,333 --> 00:02:54,533
One possible scenario

56
00:02:54,667 --> 00:02:57,400
is that the Vice Mayor
was shot while sitting.

57
00:02:59,267 --> 00:03:01,133
Bok, what's the plan?

58
00:03:02,933 --> 00:03:04,600
I need to talk to the Chief.

59
00:03:10,833 --> 00:03:12,333
By the way, Doc,

60
00:03:12,467 --> 00:03:14,667
think about it carefully, okay?

61
00:03:14,800 --> 00:03:16,233
Get out, please.

62
00:03:16,367 --> 00:03:18,000
Just get out.

63
00:03:20,800 --> 00:03:22,500
Bobby, here's your coffee.

64
00:03:22,633 --> 00:03:23,733
Thank you.

65
00:03:26,033 --> 00:03:29,100
Godfather, have you heard about
what happened to the Vice Mayor?

66
00:03:30,200 --> 00:03:31,933
Is it really Victor Santiago
who killed her?

67
00:03:33,600 --> 00:03:35,633
Right now,
it's still under investigation,

68
00:03:35,767 --> 00:03:38,000
but I want you to know,
Godfather,

69
00:03:38,133 --> 00:03:40,200
that there's a big chance
that we'll get justice

70
00:03:40,333 --> 00:03:41,933
for what happened to godmother.

71
00:03:42,067 --> 00:03:43,700
What do you mean?

72
00:03:43,833 --> 00:03:47,367
Was Amo involved in the
San Isidro bank robbery?

73
00:03:48,967 --> 00:03:49,967
Dad...

74
00:03:50,100 --> 00:03:50,833
Dear.

75
00:03:52,733 --> 00:03:54,333
What's she doing here?

76
00:03:54,500 --> 00:03:57,900
Reign, she's just updating us
on your mommy's case.

77
00:03:59,633 --> 00:04:03,733
Well, if you've said what you
needed to say, you can leave.

78
00:04:04,767 --> 00:04:08,767
Because no matter what you do,
you'll never get my mom back.

79
00:04:10,000 --> 00:04:11,433
Don't ever come back here.

80
00:04:12,733 --> 00:04:13,667
I know.

81
00:04:16,333 --> 00:04:17,533
I accept it...

82
00:04:19,467 --> 00:04:21,800
that if it weren't for me,

83
00:04:21,933 --> 00:04:24,567
maybe even now, Godmother Dina
would still be alive.

84
00:04:27,033 --> 00:04:28,667
Reign, I didn't want that.

85
00:04:30,567 --> 00:04:36,067
I wouldn't want the person who
became my second mother to die.

86
00:04:40,833 --> 00:04:45,333
I'm not here to force you
to forgive me either.

87
00:04:48,233 --> 00:04:50,167
Because if that happened
to me...

88
00:04:51,667 --> 00:04:53,300
I wouldn't forgive you either.

89
00:04:57,467 --> 00:05:00,767
All I want is for you to give me
a chance to make it up to you.

90
00:05:04,533 --> 00:05:07,633
I'll find whoever killed
Godmother Dina.

91
00:05:09,333 --> 00:05:11,200
And I won't stop...

92
00:05:11,333 --> 00:05:14,233
I won't stop until I bring
that person to you.

93
00:05:18,267 --> 00:05:19,133
I'll go ahead.

94
00:05:20,700 --> 00:05:21,800
Bobby...

95
00:05:35,267 --> 00:05:38,167
I miss mom so much.

96
00:05:46,967 --> 00:05:49,400
Bobby, I'm sorry.

97
00:05:56,033 --> 00:05:58,167
Mommy's gone...

98
00:06:03,000 --> 00:06:07,767
- Mommy's gone, Bobby.
- I know, I know.

99
00:06:14,800 --> 00:06:18,567
Sophia, you take care
of the campaign, okay?

100
00:06:18,700 --> 00:06:21,433
I just need to do something
about Victor's case.

101
00:06:21,567 --> 00:06:23,800
Put that aside for now, Joaquin.

102
00:06:23,933 --> 00:06:27,300
I promised the people
of Calabari peace and safety.

103
00:06:27,433 --> 00:06:31,800
That's why I'm hands-on with
Víctor's case to bring justice

104
00:06:31,933 --> 00:06:34,200
to Del Mundo's family.

105
00:06:34,333 --> 00:06:36,967
I understand you, Joaquin.

106
00:06:37,100 --> 00:06:39,133
But you also have to remember

107
00:06:39,267 --> 00:06:41,000
that the election
is coming soon.

108
00:06:41,167 --> 00:06:45,700
You have to meet your followers
so we can ensure your victory.

109
00:06:45,833 --> 00:06:47,233
Sophia...

110
00:06:47,367 --> 00:06:50,000
if Victor gets acquitted,

111
00:06:50,133 --> 00:06:53,200
it's already a sure win for me,
okay?

112
00:06:53,333 --> 00:06:54,667
Go ahead.

113
00:06:54,800 --> 00:06:56,367
Please, I need to do something.

114
00:06:56,500 --> 00:06:57,567
Okay.

115
00:07:05,767 --> 00:07:08,700
Amo, I brought you your clothes.

116
00:07:08,833 --> 00:07:10,667
And then at your arraignment
later,

117
00:07:10,800 --> 00:07:15,300
Judge Alcantara will just
explain the cases you're facing,

118
00:07:15,467 --> 00:07:16,267
okay?

119
00:07:16,400 --> 00:07:18,267
What Verns said is right,
Sir Victor.

120
00:07:18,400 --> 00:07:20,867
We'll face the prosecution
later.

121
00:07:21,000 --> 00:07:23,267
Wasn't I really allowed
to post bail?

122
00:07:23,400 --> 00:07:26,400
It depends on Judge Alcantara.

123
00:07:26,533 --> 00:07:28,200
Judge Alcantara.

124
00:07:28,333 --> 00:07:31,733
We all know that the judge
is on Joaquin's side.

125
00:07:31,867 --> 00:07:34,067
I'll be transparent with you,
Sir Víctor.

126
00:07:34,200 --> 00:07:36,000
The prosecution is strong

127
00:07:36,133 --> 00:07:37,767
because of the ballistics
report.

128
00:07:37,900 --> 00:07:41,367
So we really need to be careful
with every move and defense.

129
00:07:41,500 --> 00:07:43,033
Yes, Amo.

130
00:07:43,167 --> 00:07:45,067
How are my supporters?

131
00:07:45,200 --> 00:07:47,167
Amo, they're still there.

132
00:07:47,300 --> 00:07:49,700
And a lot of people believe
that you were just framed.

133
00:07:49,867 --> 00:07:51,500
Don't worry.

134
00:07:51,633 --> 00:07:54,567
I'm sure Joaquin will meddle
with my case.

135
00:07:55,867 --> 00:07:57,400
This is my only hope...

136
00:07:58,533 --> 00:08:00,133
the people's sympathy.

137
00:08:06,167 --> 00:08:10,533
We need to help the prosecution
by giving everything we have

138
00:08:10,667 --> 00:08:11,433
to this case.

139
00:08:12,567 --> 00:08:16,733
Even if the gun matched
the one used to kill Vice Mayor,

140
00:08:16,867 --> 00:08:19,133
it's still not enough
for the Court.

141
00:08:19,267 --> 00:08:21,667
Chief, we need
to invite Roman here.

142
00:08:23,233 --> 00:08:24,800
Sir, our problem is that

143
00:08:24,933 --> 00:08:27,900
he won't talk until we have
a warrant.

144
00:08:28,033 --> 00:08:30,367
Roman is a person of interest

145
00:08:30,500 --> 00:08:33,100
because he's connected
to Victor.

146
00:08:33,233 --> 00:08:35,933
So work on it,
Robles and Enriquez.

147
00:08:37,467 --> 00:08:38,400
- Go ahead.
- Yes, Chief.

148
00:08:49,267 --> 00:08:51,400
Chief, someone is looking
for you,

149
00:08:51,533 --> 00:08:53,067
Attorney Dimalanta.

150
00:08:53,300 --> 00:08:54,767
Let him in, Dizon.

151
00:08:56,433 --> 00:08:57,033
Attorney.

152
00:08:59,733 --> 00:09:01,067
Good morning, Major.

153
00:09:01,200 --> 00:09:04,000
Attorney Dimalanta, prosecutor.

154
00:09:04,133 --> 00:09:05,633
Attorney, this is my team.

155
00:09:06,700 --> 00:09:08,667
Garcia, Conde, and Dizon.

156
00:09:10,667 --> 00:09:12,767
Please accompany
Attorney Dimalanta

157
00:09:12,900 --> 00:09:15,400
to get Selena's testimony.

158
00:09:15,533 --> 00:09:16,267
Attorney...

159
00:09:17,367 --> 00:09:18,600
they'll take care of you.

160
00:09:20,867 --> 00:09:21,600
Thank you.

161
00:09:22,867 --> 00:09:23,600
Okay.

162
00:09:23,867 --> 00:09:26,533
Dizon, Conde, go with Attorney
Dimalanta.

163
00:09:27,600 --> 00:09:28,933
Go ahead, Dizon, I'll follow.

164
00:09:34,200 --> 00:09:35,033
Why, Conde?

165
00:09:36,300 --> 00:09:39,367
Sir, are you sure you can trust
that person?

166
00:09:39,500 --> 00:09:41,433
What if he's also one
of Victor's men?

167
00:09:41,567 --> 00:09:45,000
Do you believe that your father
is guilty?

168
00:09:53,033 --> 00:09:53,833
Sir Fred!

169
00:09:53,967 --> 00:09:54,833
Sir Fred!

170
00:09:54,967 --> 00:09:57,233
Just a moment,
I need you to sign something.

171
00:09:57,367 --> 00:10:00,433
Attorney, I'm sorry.
I didn't see you.

172
00:10:00,600 --> 00:10:01,700
Are you okay?

173
00:10:01,833 --> 00:10:03,733
It's okay, it's okay.

174
00:10:03,867 --> 00:10:04,800
I'm sorry.

175
00:10:04,933 --> 00:10:06,367
- Nothing to worry about.
- I was in a hurry.

176
00:10:06,500 --> 00:10:08,300
Robles, what happened?

177
00:10:08,433 --> 00:10:09,500
Bro, I'm sorry.

178
00:10:09,633 --> 00:10:10,833
I bumped into Attorney.

179
00:10:10,967 --> 00:10:12,200
Are you okay, Attorney?

180
00:10:12,333 --> 00:10:13,000
It's okay.

181
00:10:13,133 --> 00:10:14,400
Nothing to worry about.

182
00:10:14,533 --> 00:10:15,933
Have you seen Enriquez?

183
00:10:16,067 --> 00:10:17,400
She's inside.

184
00:10:19,033 --> 00:10:19,567
Okay.

185
00:10:19,700 --> 00:10:20,467
Attorney, I'm sorry again.

186
00:10:20,600 --> 00:10:21,267
No worries.

187
00:10:21,400 --> 00:10:21,967
Bro...

188
00:10:22,100 --> 00:10:23,567
Come on, Attorney. Let's go.

189
00:10:27,800 --> 00:10:29,267
It's not like that, Sir.

190
00:10:30,900 --> 00:10:34,100
But if Selena is the key
to all the truth...

191
00:10:36,133 --> 00:10:38,400
I want to make sure she's safe.

192
00:10:38,533 --> 00:10:40,067
I understand you, Conde.

193
00:10:41,133 --> 00:10:42,700
But don't worry,

194
00:10:42,833 --> 00:10:46,000
because the Mayor himself
vouched for Attorney.

195
00:10:47,067 --> 00:10:47,767
Go ahead.

196
00:10:49,233 --> 00:10:50,167
Yes, Sir.

197
00:10:59,200 --> 00:11:03,067
Enriquez, just be calm.

198
00:11:03,200 --> 00:11:05,267
Let me handle the conversation
with Roman.

199
00:11:05,400 --> 00:11:06,633
Yes, Sir.

200
00:11:06,767 --> 00:11:11,500
Sir, I hope this is our big
break in all the cases we have.

201
00:11:11,667 --> 00:11:14,600
I have a strong feeling
that all of this is connected.

202
00:11:14,733 --> 00:11:15,933
I hope you're right.

203
00:11:17,767 --> 00:11:18,633
Let's go.

204
00:11:24,900 --> 00:11:26,233
Hello, Godfather?

205
00:11:26,367 --> 00:11:28,067
Is there a problem?

206
00:11:28,200 --> 00:11:30,367
Bobby, help me.

207
00:11:30,500 --> 00:11:31,467
It's Reign.

208
00:11:31,600 --> 00:11:33,400
Okay, Godfather,
I'm on my way there.

209
00:11:34,900 --> 00:11:37,067
Sir, I can't go with you.

210
00:11:37,200 --> 00:11:39,067
Don't tell me you have
a personal errand.

211
00:11:39,200 --> 00:11:41,033
My godfather needs me.
It's an emergency.

212
00:11:41,200 --> 00:11:43,067
What am I going to tell Chief
when he asks for you?

213
00:11:43,200 --> 00:11:45,400
I'll explain it to him.
I'm sorry.

214
00:11:45,533 --> 00:11:46,500
- Enriquez!
- I'll go ahead.

215
00:12:09,200 --> 00:12:10,900
You're alone?

216
00:12:11,033 --> 00:12:12,800
Where's your companion
who is more arrogant

217
00:12:12,933 --> 00:12:13,700
than the two of us?

218
00:12:15,367 --> 00:12:16,467
I'll send you a link.

219
00:12:16,600 --> 00:12:17,400
Check it out.

220
00:12:19,233 --> 00:12:21,300
What's this nonsense again?

221
00:12:24,833 --> 00:12:25,700
Hey...

222
00:12:27,000 --> 00:12:28,200
what's this?

223
00:12:28,333 --> 00:12:30,033
I put a tracker on someone
earlier.

224
00:12:31,733 --> 00:12:34,533
<i>Attorney, I'm sorry.
I didn't see you.</i>

225
00:12:35,567 --> 00:12:36,233
Who?

226
00:12:36,367 --> 00:12:38,533
The prosecution attorney.

227
00:12:38,667 --> 00:12:41,467
They're on their way to the
safehouse to talk to Selena.

228
00:12:47,100 --> 00:12:49,400
Hello, Selena...

229
00:13:05,400 --> 00:13:06,933
<i>The subscriber cannot
be reached.</i>

230
00:13:07,067 --> 00:13:07,867
<i> Please try...</i>

231
00:13:08,000 --> 00:13:08,633
Godfather!

232
00:13:09,833 --> 00:13:11,567
What are you saying
about Reign being missing?

233
00:13:11,700 --> 00:13:13,767
Didn't you see her
with her luggage earlier?

234
00:13:13,900 --> 00:13:16,233
Her flight to Hong Kong
is today.

235
00:13:16,367 --> 00:13:18,600
It's just a little over
two hours away.

236
00:13:18,733 --> 00:13:20,567
Bobby, it's almost four hours
already.

237
00:13:20,700 --> 00:13:22,433
I can't contact Reign.

238
00:13:22,600 --> 00:13:23,600
She hasn't updated me yet.

239
00:13:23,733 --> 00:13:25,367
She's not like that.

240
00:13:25,500 --> 00:13:27,500
Godfather, have you checked
her flight status?

241
00:13:27,633 --> 00:13:28,733
That's the problem.

242
00:13:28,867 --> 00:13:30,500
She'll only get her ticket

243
00:13:30,633 --> 00:13:32,133
when she gets to the recruitment
agency,

244
00:13:32,267 --> 00:13:33,633
but I can't contact her.

245
00:13:33,767 --> 00:13:35,033
How about the travel agency?

246
00:13:35,167 --> 00:13:36,200
Have you called them yet,
Godfather?

247
00:13:36,333 --> 00:13:37,667
Here, I've been calling them
for a while now,

248
00:13:37,800 --> 00:13:38,400
but no one's answering.

249
00:13:38,567 --> 00:13:39,967
Godfather, let me see.

250
00:13:40,100 --> 00:13:40,667
Here.

251
00:13:47,133 --> 00:13:48,000
- I'll go ahead.
- Thank you.

252
00:13:53,767 --> 00:13:54,600
Reign...

253
00:14:09,433 --> 00:14:10,067
Sir.

254
00:14:12,733 --> 00:14:13,667
How's everyone doing?

255
00:14:13,800 --> 00:14:15,100
We're okay, Sir.

256
00:14:17,000 --> 00:14:18,700
Attorney is with me.

257
00:14:18,833 --> 00:14:20,300
He wants to talk to Selena.

258
00:14:20,433 --> 00:14:22,033
Go ahead, she's inside.

259
00:14:23,567 --> 00:14:25,300
Attorney, let's go.

260
00:14:26,333 --> 00:14:27,500
Bok, we'll just go in.

261
00:14:35,000 --> 00:14:36,300
How's everyone doing?

262
00:14:36,433 --> 00:14:38,433
We're okay, Sir. We're all safe.

263
00:14:38,567 --> 00:14:39,267
Sir.

264
00:14:44,567 --> 00:14:45,767
Wait a minute.

265
00:14:50,733 --> 00:14:53,267
Sir Tonyo, come in.

266
00:14:53,400 --> 00:14:55,167
Selena,

267
00:14:55,300 --> 00:14:57,667
Attorney Dimalanta is with me.

268
00:14:57,800 --> 00:14:59,133
He's the one who's going
to interview you.

269
00:15:00,567 --> 00:15:01,667
Hello, Attorney.

270
00:15:01,833 --> 00:15:02,667
Selena.

271
00:15:02,800 --> 00:15:03,867
Attorney Dimalanta.

272
00:15:04,967 --> 00:15:07,433
Attorney, let me leave you two
alone.

273
00:15:07,567 --> 00:15:08,433
I'll take care of it.

274
00:15:09,800 --> 00:15:11,100
Selena, I'll be right outside.

275
00:15:11,233 --> 00:15:12,733
Okay, Sir Tonyo. Thank you.

276
00:15:43,667 --> 00:15:45,033
Good morning.

277
00:15:45,167 --> 00:15:46,333
Excuse me.

278
00:15:46,467 --> 00:15:47,867
Can I...

279
00:15:48,000 --> 00:15:49,400
- Can I ask a question?
- Okay.

280
00:15:51,167 --> 00:15:53,367
Is this the right address
for this?

281
00:15:53,500 --> 00:15:54,400
Starfire?

282
00:15:55,433 --> 00:15:56,767
There's nothing like that here,
Ma'am.

283
00:15:58,233 --> 00:15:59,467
Are you sure?

284
00:15:59,600 --> 00:16:00,433
Yes.

285
00:16:00,567 --> 00:16:01,767
Is the address
you were given correct?

286
00:16:05,567 --> 00:16:08,233
Mister, that CCTV,
is that yours?

287
00:16:08,400 --> 00:16:09,600
Ma'am, that's not ours.

288
00:16:09,733 --> 00:16:10,900
That belongs
to the other tenant.

289
00:16:12,200 --> 00:16:13,233
Okay, thank you.

290
00:16:13,367 --> 00:16:14,000
Okay.

291
00:16:25,500 --> 00:16:27,400
Good morning, Mister.

292
00:16:27,533 --> 00:16:28,400
Yes, Ma'am?

293
00:16:29,767 --> 00:16:31,533
I'm Sergeant Enriquez.

294
00:16:32,800 --> 00:16:34,567
I'm investigating a case.

295
00:16:36,400 --> 00:16:38,400
Is your CCTV working?

296
00:16:38,533 --> 00:16:39,533
Yes.

297
00:16:39,667 --> 00:16:42,533
Can I check the CCTV footage
inside?

298
00:16:42,700 --> 00:16:44,200
Okay, this way.

299
00:16:44,333 --> 00:16:45,233
Okay.

300
00:16:50,133 --> 00:16:50,933
Selena...

301
00:16:52,133 --> 00:16:53,467
I'll go straight to the point.

302
00:16:54,567 --> 00:16:55,733
Can we start now?

303
00:16:56,833 --> 00:16:58,100
Yes, okay.

304
00:16:58,233 --> 00:17:01,467
I will tell you everything
you need to know

305
00:17:01,600 --> 00:17:05,067
so that Amo takes responsibility
for all the crimes he committed.

306
00:17:05,200 --> 00:17:09,100
Attorney, I really believe that
he killed my boyfriend, Sonny.

307
00:17:10,233 --> 00:17:11,767
Okay.

308
00:17:11,900 --> 00:17:13,967
Let's start with your boyfriend.

309
00:17:14,100 --> 00:17:17,500
I believe his name is Sonny,
right?

310
00:17:19,100 --> 00:17:22,733
Can you tell me how you two met?

311
00:17:27,467 --> 00:17:28,100
Yes.

312
00:17:32,467 --> 00:17:35,700
I was performing
close to them before.

313
00:17:35,833 --> 00:17:41,333
And then a friend of mine
introduced him to me.

314
00:17:45,933 --> 00:17:48,733
You take care of Attorney
and Selena, okay?

315
00:17:48,900 --> 00:17:49,900
Yes, Sir.

316
00:17:50,033 --> 00:17:52,133
Okay, Sir. Be careful.

317
00:17:53,633 --> 00:17:54,333
Let's go.

318
00:17:56,767 --> 00:17:59,467
Do you think Amo
is really guilty?

319
00:18:01,233 --> 00:18:02,267
If he's guilty...

320
00:18:03,767 --> 00:18:06,467
then this might be connected
to the San Isidro bank robbery.

321
00:18:09,200 --> 00:18:10,667
I just want to know
what the truth is...

322
00:18:11,833 --> 00:18:13,633
so I can give Lara justice.

323
00:18:15,933 --> 00:18:18,567
Selena's role is going
to be important,

324
00:18:18,700 --> 00:18:20,533
especially when the hearing
comes.

325
00:18:26,300 --> 00:18:27,300
Who are these people?

326
00:18:38,633 --> 00:18:39,400
Attorney?

327
00:18:57,267 --> 00:18:58,867
Stay here, Miss Selena.

328
00:18:59,000 --> 00:18:59,800
Stay here.

329
00:18:59,933 --> 00:19:01,167
No...

330
00:19:01,300 --> 00:19:03,067
Just calm down,
just calm down.

331
00:19:04,233 --> 00:19:05,433
Just calm down.

332
00:19:31,033 --> 00:19:32,000
Sergeant...

333
00:19:34,233 --> 00:19:37,433
this is a copy of the CCTV
footage from 5 hours ago.

334
00:19:54,800 --> 00:19:55,967
This is right.

335
00:20:13,733 --> 00:20:14,833
Hi, Reign!

336
00:20:17,500 --> 00:20:18,633
Reign, right?

337
00:20:18,767 --> 00:20:19,867
Yes, that's me.

338
00:20:20,000 --> 00:20:21,500
Are you the one I was talking
to on the cellphone?

339
00:20:21,633 --> 00:20:23,167
Yes, it's me you were talking
to on the phone.

340
00:20:23,300 --> 00:20:24,367
Madelyn.

341
00:20:24,500 --> 00:20:26,900
-I'm the head of HR at Starfire.
-Hi.

342
00:20:27,033 --> 00:20:27,733
Okay.

343
00:20:29,200 --> 00:20:30,367
So, are you ready?

344
00:20:30,500 --> 00:20:32,333
Or maybe you forgot
to do something?

345
00:20:33,800 --> 00:20:35,067
Where are we going?

346
00:20:35,200 --> 00:20:36,700
Isn't this your office?

347
00:20:36,867 --> 00:20:38,967
I'm sorry, I forgot to explain.

348
00:20:39,100 --> 00:20:41,033
Starfire has a new office.

349
00:20:41,167 --> 00:20:43,867
So I'll take you and your
companions there.

350
00:20:46,167 --> 00:20:48,767
Ma'am, can I see the ticket
first?

351
00:20:48,900 --> 00:20:50,800
Well, that's the thing,
it's in the office too.

352
00:20:50,933 --> 00:20:53,367
So, you okay? You good?
Let's go.

353
00:20:55,667 --> 00:20:56,467
Okay.

354
00:21:01,867 --> 00:21:03,100
What? Let's go.

355
00:21:06,467 --> 00:21:07,333
Okay.

356
00:21:43,267 --> 00:21:44,967
Hello, Noble.

357
00:21:45,100 --> 00:21:46,967
Call our contact
in the traffic team.

358
00:21:47,100 --> 00:21:48,967
Tell them to trace this vehicle.

359
00:21:49,100 --> 00:21:50,367
A black van.

360
00:21:50,500 --> 00:21:53,567
Delta, alpha, x-ray, 3-6-4-9.

361
00:21:53,700 --> 00:21:54,800
Get back to me right away, okay?

362
00:22:05,033 --> 00:22:07,533
Sir Tonyo, Sir Tonyo.

363
00:22:07,667 --> 00:22:09,433
- No.
- Let's call him. Let's call...

364
00:22:19,267 --> 00:22:21,900
Don't! No! Don't kill me,
don't kill me.

365
00:22:22,033 --> 00:22:23,533
Do you want to go with him?

366
00:22:23,667 --> 00:22:24,867
I don't want to.

367
00:22:34,833 --> 00:22:35,833
Hurry up!

368
00:22:35,967 --> 00:22:37,000
Don't be stubborn!

369
00:22:37,133 --> 00:22:37,600
Hurry up!

370
00:22:38,867 --> 00:22:39,800
Hurry up!

371
00:22:39,933 --> 00:22:40,867
Let me go!

372
00:22:41,000 --> 00:22:42,333
- Come here! Come!
- Help!

373
00:22:42,467 --> 00:22:44,433
- So stubborn! I'll kill you!
- Help!

374
00:22:44,567 --> 00:22:46,067
- Help me!
- Hurry!

375
00:22:46,200 --> 00:22:47,333
It's Selena!

376
00:22:47,467 --> 00:22:48,167
Get in!

377
00:22:50,233 --> 00:22:51,633
Let's go!

378
00:22:53,200 --> 00:22:53,967
Hurry!

379
00:22:57,467 --> 00:22:58,733
Dizon, let's go!

380
00:23:05,800 --> 00:23:06,567
Let's go!

381
00:23:22,600 --> 00:23:23,600
Hello, Noble?

382
00:23:23,733 --> 00:23:24,900
Any updates?

383
00:23:25,033 --> 00:23:27,200
Our troops spotted the vehicle,
Ma'am.

384
00:23:27,333 --> 00:23:28,967
Where did the van go?
Did you see it?

385
00:23:29,100 --> 00:23:30,167
Yes, Ma'am.

386
00:23:30,300 --> 00:23:31,667
What is this about?

387
00:23:31,800 --> 00:23:34,967
It seems like my godsister
was a victim of a fake agency.

388
00:23:35,100 --> 00:23:36,367
Where did the van go?

389
00:23:44,033 --> 00:23:45,867
- Let me go!
- Hurry!

390
00:23:46,000 --> 00:23:48,033
- Go down!
- That's enough!

391
00:23:48,167 --> 00:23:49,567
Okay, bring her in! Hurry!

392
00:23:49,700 --> 00:23:52,400
I don't want!
Where are you taking me?

393
00:23:52,533 --> 00:23:54,033
Let me go!

394
00:24:08,100 --> 00:24:09,900
<i>The subscriber cannot
be reached.</i>

395
00:24:10,033 --> 00:24:11,333
- Please try again later.
- I can't contact the Chief.

396
00:24:18,800 --> 00:24:20,533
- Sir!
- Enriquez!

397
00:24:20,667 --> 00:24:22,167
What are you doing here?

398
00:24:22,300 --> 00:24:23,967
Sir, my godsister was kidnapped.

399
00:24:24,100 --> 00:24:26,367
I had Noble trace the van.
He said it was brought here.

400
00:24:27,833 --> 00:24:29,500
How about you, Sir,
what are you doing here?

401
00:24:30,867 --> 00:24:32,967
Selena was kidnapped
from the safehouse.

402
00:24:33,100 --> 00:24:34,200
She was brought here.

403
00:24:34,333 --> 00:24:35,700
She was brought here, too?

404
00:24:37,100 --> 00:24:40,100
What connection does Reign's
kidnapping have to Selena's?

405
00:24:41,200 --> 00:24:42,133
I don't know either.

406
00:24:43,433 --> 00:24:45,300
What's important is that
we save them.

407
00:24:46,633 --> 00:24:47,667
How, Sir?

408
00:24:49,867 --> 00:24:51,833
Let's go there. Come on.

409
00:24:57,033 --> 00:24:58,967
Let me go!

410
00:24:59,100 --> 00:25:00,133
Please!

411
00:25:00,267 --> 00:25:01,367
I'm begging you!

412
00:25:01,500 --> 00:25:02,500
Sir, listen to me.

413
00:25:02,667 --> 00:25:03,767
Let me go.

414
00:25:03,900 --> 00:25:06,467
Promise, I won't say anything
against Amo.

415
00:25:06,767 --> 00:25:07,433
I'll hide.

416
00:25:07,567 --> 00:25:08,900
You'll never see me again.

417
00:25:09,033 --> 00:25:10,533
You're so stubborn.

418
00:25:10,800 --> 00:25:11,467
You've been annoying
for a while.

419
00:25:11,600 --> 00:25:12,933
I'm pissed off with you.

420
00:25:13,067 --> 00:25:15,767
You can't escape.
Do you understand?

421
00:25:15,900 --> 00:25:18,100
Okay, bring her inside.

422
00:25:18,233 --> 00:25:19,133
Let's go!

423
00:25:19,267 --> 00:25:21,633
No! Have mercy on me! Please!

424
00:25:33,300 --> 00:25:34,167
It's Reign.

425
00:25:34,300 --> 00:25:35,367
Enriquez, wait a minute.

426
00:25:36,433 --> 00:25:38,733
Don't be so hasty.

427
00:25:38,867 --> 00:25:40,533
Boss, what are we going
to do with these?

428
00:25:40,667 --> 00:25:41,967
Get those ready.

429
00:25:42,100 --> 00:25:43,833
Later, we'll take them
somewhere.

430
00:25:43,967 --> 00:25:45,500
Okay, bring them up.

431
00:25:45,633 --> 00:25:46,767
Let's go.

432
00:25:46,900 --> 00:25:47,800
Sir!

433
00:25:55,000 --> 00:25:56,100
Let's go.

434
00:26:04,133 --> 00:26:04,733
Hey!

435
00:26:20,867 --> 00:26:22,367
They got Selena.

436
00:26:22,500 --> 00:26:23,433
How did that happen?

437
00:26:23,567 --> 00:26:26,033
Dizon and I don't know
how they got the address.

438
00:26:26,267 --> 00:26:27,667
But I have a hunch that Selena
is right.

439
00:26:27,800 --> 00:26:29,767
There's a spy here
at our station.

440
00:26:29,900 --> 00:26:30,767
What do you mean?

441
00:26:30,900 --> 00:26:32,367
Is Amo involved in this?

442
00:26:32,500 --> 00:26:33,567
If he's involved in this,

443
00:26:33,700 --> 00:26:36,900
then he's part of the human
trafficking syndicate

444
00:26:37,033 --> 00:26:38,500
that kidnapped my godsister.

445
00:26:38,633 --> 00:26:40,667
Bobby, please give Reign
back to me.

446
00:26:40,800 --> 00:26:42,100
Lieutenant Conde,
any updates?

447
00:26:42,267 --> 00:26:44,533
The Chief is expediting
our visas.

448
00:26:44,667 --> 00:26:45,933
Why? Where are we going?

449
00:26:46,067 --> 00:26:47,733
We're flying to Dubai.

450
00:26:47,867 --> 00:26:50,400
We're almost near the building
my contact mentioned.

451
00:26:50,533 --> 00:26:52,067
The women are being dropped off

452
00:26:52,200 --> 00:26:53,467
in the basement
of that building.

453
00:26:53,600 --> 00:26:54,433
There's an entrance and exit

454
00:26:54,567 --> 00:26:55,900
at the front and back
of the building.

455
00:26:56,033 --> 00:26:57,733
We need to cover
the front and back.

456
00:26:57,867 --> 00:26:59,467
Enriquez, come with me.
Let's go to the front.

457
00:26:59,600 --> 00:27:00,567
Conde, go to the back.

458
00:27:00,700 --> 00:27:01,967
Hey!

459
00:27:02,100 --> 00:27:03,300
You're not allowed here.

460
00:27:03,433 --> 00:27:04,733
Stop!

461
00:27:04,867 --> 00:27:06,033
Who are you?
